# install Rancher Kubernetes Engine (RKE)
https://rke.docs.rancher.com/installation

prerequisite:
------------
1) Build Machine
2) Node instalation and configuration (1 master, 2 workers)
3) Download rke binary
https://github.com/rancher/rke/releases
4) $ chmod +x rke ; cp rke /usr/sbin
5) rke --help


6) Install kubectl cli

7) Container runtime on all the cluster node

Note:
 master0 192.168.56.1
 worker0 192.168.56.2
 worker1 192.168.56.3
 
 
Password less autnentication to all the node:
$ build> ssh-copy-id master0
         ssh-copy-id worker0
         ssh-copy-id worker1


